24/10/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Interior Minister Rumen Petkov announced on Friday (21 October) he appointed replacements for four deputy chiefs of the National Service for Organised Crime Fighting (NSOCF) who resigned earlier in the week. Among them is Donka Georgieva, the first woman appointed to management of the anti-mafia body. 
On Saturday meanwhile, regional NSOCF departments in Haskovo and Stara Zagora smashed a drug trafficking channel, seizing 51kgs of amphetamines worth over 3m euros. (Dnevnik - 23/10/05; bTV - 22/10/05)
